00:00:53.650 --> 00:00:55.980 align:middle line:84%
His breadth of understanding
is vast and deep.

00:00:55.980 --> 00:00:58.410 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to discuss
one of the primary challenges

00:00:58.410 --> 00:00:59.510 align:middle line:90%
of being human.

00:00:59.510 --> 00:01:01.780 align:middle line:84%
How to live a sovereign
and meaningful life

00:01:01.780 --> 00:01:04.660 align:middle line:90%
amidst a world of distraction.

00:01:04.660 --> 00:01:07.460 align:middle line:84%
I think everybody watching
this will probably

00:01:07.460 --> 00:01:09.210 align:middle line:84%
want to know the
trick to that one.

00:01:09.210 --> 00:01:10.370 align:middle line:90%
But it's not a trick.

00:01:10.370 --> 00:01:11.120 align:middle line:90%
>>NEIL KRAMER: No.

00:01:11.120 --> 00:01:11.990 align:middle line:90%
It isn't a trick.

00:01:11.990 --> 00:01:12.990 align:middle line:90%
It's an art form.

00:01:12.990 --> 00:01:14.350 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's an art form.

00:01:14.350 --> 00:01:17.620 align:middle line:84%
And let's start out, because
we're going to-- I'll

00:01:17.620 --> 00:01:19.200 align:middle line:84%
lead into this in
a minute, but let's

00:01:19.200 --> 00:01:23.880 align:middle line:84%
talk about the nature of
this ritualistic, almost

00:01:23.880 --> 00:01:27.340 align:middle line:84%
kind of zombie-like life that
the vast majority of humanity

00:01:27.340 --> 00:01:29.240 align:middle line:90%
is participating in.

00:01:29.240 --> 00:01:32.220 align:middle line:10%
>>KRAMER: A good
visual metaphor for it

00:01:32.220 --> 00:01:35.940 align:middle line:10%
is to say that a lot
routines and patterns in life

00:01:35.940 --> 00:01:37.590 align:middle line:10%
are kind of like train tracks.

00:01:37.590 --> 00:01:41.790 align:middle line:10%
And there's various stops
on the subway, as it were.

00:01:41.790 --> 00:01:43.540 align:middle line:10%
And people become
accustomed to those

00:01:43.540 --> 00:01:48.720 align:middle line:10%
and they regard many stops
on the subway as choice.

00:01:48.720 --> 00:01:51.330 align:middle line:84%
As free will,
forgetting the fact

00:01:51.330 --> 00:01:53.140 align:middle line:84%
that they are actually
all predetermined.

00:01:53.140 --> 00:01:53.940 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And they're
all in the sa--

00:01:53.940 --> 00:01:55.620 align:middle line:84%
they're going the
same line every day.

00:01:55.620 --> 00:01:57.400 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: To the
same line every day.

00:01:57.400 --> 00:01:57.990 align:middle line:90%
You get on it.

00:01:57.990 --> 00:01:58.550 align:middle line:90%
You do this.

00:01:58.550 --> 00:01:59.100 align:middle line:90%
You do this.

00:01:59.100 --> 00:02:00.080 align:middle line:90%
You do this.

00:02:00.080 --> 00:02:02.510 align:middle line:84%
That choice is
mistaken for free will.

00:02:02.510 --> 00:02:03.640 align:middle line:90%
Different thing.

00:02:03.640 --> 00:02:07.635 align:middle line:84%
So there's a great
understanding in the mysticism

00:02:07.635 --> 00:02:10.699 align:middle line:84%
that I'm going to talk to
you about today in that that

00:02:10.699 --> 00:02:13.840 align:middle line:84%
has to be disposed of
as fast as possible,

00:02:13.840 --> 00:02:15.680 align:middle line:84%
which means getting
off the tracks.

00:02:15.680 --> 00:02:18.540 align:middle line:84%
Which is a very unsettling
and disturbing business

00:02:18.540 --> 00:02:19.770 align:middle line:90%
for a lot of people.

00:02:19.770 --> 00:02:24.030 align:middle line:84%
So part of my role, self
avowed and self proclaimed,

00:02:24.030 --> 00:02:26.680 align:middle line:84%
is to try and make that
achievable and approachable.

00:02:26.680 --> 00:02:29.840 align:middle line:84%
And say, only, in fact,
by getting off the rails,

00:02:29.840 --> 00:02:33.010 align:middle line:84%
getting off the tracks,
can you do anything.

00:02:33.010 --> 00:02:34.380 align:middle line:90%
Otherwise it's too inconsistent.

00:02:34.380 --> 00:02:36.720 align:middle line:90%


00:02:36.720 --> 00:02:38.220 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Do you
feel that there has

00:02:38.220 --> 00:02:41.160 align:middle line:84%
to be a moment of
shaking, or awakening,

00:02:41.160 --> 00:02:43.610 align:middle line:84%
or disruption in
one's life to create

00:02:43.610 --> 00:02:45.812 align:middle line:84%
the necessity for
breaking patterns?

00:02:45.812 --> 00:02:47.020 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Yeah, either a de--

00:02:47.020 --> 00:02:48.710 align:middle line:90%
We'll stress the metaphor.

00:02:48.710 --> 00:02:52.530 align:middle line:84%
Either a derailment
or such soul numbing

00:02:52.530 --> 00:02:54.870 align:middle line:84%
repetition that
typically at the age--

00:02:54.870 --> 00:02:56.370 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's too
painful to go on.

00:02:56.370 --> 00:02:57.420 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Yeah.

00:02:57.420 --> 00:03:00.480 align:middle line:84%
You have a midlife crisis,
whether it's at 25 or 55,

00:03:00.480 --> 00:03:02.640 align:middle line:84%
and you think, why
am I doing this?

00:03:02.640 --> 00:03:05.670 align:middle line:84%
Is this something that
brings me fulfillment?

00:03:05.670 --> 00:03:07.960 align:middle line:90%
Is it aligned with my growth?

00:03:07.960 --> 00:03:11.061 align:middle line:84%
Is it something that
I'm supposed to do?

00:03:11.061 --> 00:03:13.060 align:middle line:84%
And is anyone holding a
gun to your head saying,

00:03:13.060 --> 00:03:14.410 align:middle line:90%
you must do this?

00:03:14.410 --> 00:03:16.545 align:middle line:84%
And it's typically something
that people suppress.

00:03:16.545 --> 00:03:19.510 align:middle line:84%
And culture asks us
to suppress that.

00:03:19.510 --> 00:03:22.630 align:middle line:84%
So my view is that
I agree with you.

00:03:22.630 --> 00:03:24.200 align:middle line:90%
It usually takes something.

00:03:24.200 --> 00:03:27.910 align:middle line:84%
But then it requires a great
fortitude, which we'll come to,

00:03:27.910 --> 00:03:29.670 align:middle line:90%
to actually sustain that.

00:03:29.670 --> 00:03:33.472 align:middle line:84%
Because everyone has moments
of epiphany and realization,

00:03:33.472 --> 00:03:35.430 align:middle line:84%
but then it goes away
and you're back on track.

00:03:35.430 --> 00:03:37.550 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Then it actually
has to be a choice point.

00:03:37.550 --> 00:03:39.580 align:middle line:84%
One of the things we're
going to show in a minute

00:03:39.580 --> 00:03:41.413 align:middle line:84%
is-- we're going to
show a video in a minute

00:03:41.413 --> 00:03:45.870 align:middle line:84%
because it is so illustrative
of how we live our lives

00:03:45.870 --> 00:03:47.180 align:middle line:90%
and how we're influenced.

00:03:47.180 --> 00:03:51.080 align:middle line:84%
And you have watched
the illusionist-- Is he

00:03:51.080 --> 00:03:52.580 align:middle line:84%
called an illusionist,
Derren Brown?

00:03:52.580 --> 00:03:53.530 align:middle line:90%
>>KRAMER: Yeah.

00:03:53.530 --> 00:03:55.696 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: An illusionist,
for lack of a better word.

00:03:55.696 --> 00:03:58.170 align:middle line:84%
I think, last I heard,
28 million people a week

00:03:58.170 --> 00:04:00.660 align:middle line:90%
watch his shows in England.

00:04:00.660 --> 00:04:03.520 align:middle line:84%
And the man is
incredibly masterful.

00:04:03.520 --> 00:04:06.020 align:middle line:84%
And what is it--
why did you start

00:04:06.020 --> 00:04:09.300 align:middle line:84%
studying-- kind of
studying his ways

00:04:09.300 --> 00:04:11.660 align:middle line:84%
and watching what
he's doing by way

00:04:11.660 --> 00:04:13.112 align:middle line:90%
of manipulating the populace?

00:04:13.112 --> 00:04:14.820 align:middle line:84%
>>KRAMER: Well, it's
a classic technique,

00:04:14.820 --> 00:04:17.200 align:middle line:84%
which is you choose something
safe, that's entertaining,

00:04:17.200 --> 00:04:20.670 align:middle line:84%
to demonstrate a very
big, profound principle.

00:04:20.670 --> 00:04:25.840 align:middle line:84%
So this guy has entertainment
shows in England.

00:04:25.840 --> 00:04:29.970 align:middle line:84%
And wider UK, Scotland,
Europe-- all over the place.

00:04:29.970 --> 00:04:31.590 align:middle line:90%
Now in America.

00:04:31.590 --> 00:04:36.130 align:middle line:84%
And he takes the principal
of the train track,

00:04:36.130 --> 00:04:40.110 align:middle line:84%
and he introduces a moment of
confusion to reroute somebody.

00:04:40.110 --> 00:04:42.510 align:middle line:84%
So you know, like on the
track, you have the switches.

00:04:42.510 --> 00:04:44.710 align:middle line:84%
And he knows when
someone's approaching that,

00:04:44.710 --> 00:04:46.620 align:middle line:90%
and he pulls the switch on them.

00:04:46.620 --> 00:04:49.170 align:middle line:84%
And predetermines where
they're going to go.

00:04:49.170 --> 00:04:51.790 align:middle line:84%
To the viewer, it looks
like mind control.

00:04:51.790 --> 00:04:54.430 align:middle line:90%
And in a very real way, it is.

00:04:54.430 --> 00:04:58.620 align:middle line:84%
So he introduces a whole new
generation of 20, and 30,

00:04:58.620 --> 00:05:03.240 align:middle line:84%
and 40 and 50-year olds
to real life mind control.

00:05:03.240 --> 00:05:06.420 align:middle line:84%
And it's notable how,
when you take that out

00:05:06.420 --> 00:05:10.240 align:middle line:84%
of the guy's skill
in entertainment,

00:05:10.240 --> 00:05:12.410 align:middle line:84%
and apply it to
the television, you

00:05:12.410 --> 00:05:15.330 align:middle line:84%
realize the same thing
is being done there

00:05:15.330 --> 00:05:17.950 align:middle line:84%
as it is in the
universities and colleges.

00:05:17.950 --> 00:05:18.940 align:middle line:90%
In the home.

00:05:18.940 --> 00:05:20.220 align:middle line:90%
In the elementary school.

00:05:20.220 --> 00:05:21.010 align:middle line:90%
In the workplace.

00:05:21.010 --> 00:05:22.490 align:middle line:90%
It's the same thing.

00:05:22.490 --> 00:05:24.840 align:middle line:84%
They are doing a
Derren Brown on you.

00:05:24.840 --> 00:05:27.610 align:middle line:84%
So understanding
the mechanism makes

00:05:27.610 --> 00:05:29.290 align:middle line:90%
it harder to be controlled.

00:05:29.290 --> 00:05:30.980 align:middle line:84%
And it is the modern
version of it.

00:05:30.980 --> 00:05:33.430 align:middle line:84%
There's a guy from--
Milton Erickson--

00:05:33.430 --> 00:05:36.810 align:middle line:84%
there's other people in the past
who he's developing their work.

00:05:36.810 --> 00:05:39.365 align:middle line:84%
I'm sure he wouldn't
mind others knowing that.

00:05:39.365 --> 00:05:42.030 align:middle line:84%
But he's the contemporary
practitioner.

00:05:42.030 --> 00:05:43.530 align:middle line:84%
So I think people
are going to enjoy

00:05:43.530 --> 00:05:44.250 align:middle line:90%
the clip you're going to show.

00:05:44.250 --> 00:05:44.590 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:05:44.590 --> 00:05:44.940 align:middle line:90%
OK.

